+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S2-P03-T029 (backup-restore + data-lifecycle drill; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Twenty-ninth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S2-P03), one task per run. Goal: rehearse backup-restore and the data lifecycle -- prove a 2016 month, a 2020 month, and the current month all recover, and make explicit which data is permanent versus regenerable. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; the drill restores into an isolated in-memory SQLite (the T025 DocumentVersion schema) and never touches production D1 or R2. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/restore_drill.py (restore a month's documents and versions from the T027 open snapshot into an isolated SQLite, referentially closed so every version's parent document is pulled in even across month partitions; link the permanent raw artifacts; verify counts, relationships, and random body and attachment; and enforce the retention policy -- permanent stores stay read-only with zero permanent deletes), RESTORE_RUNBOOK.md, RETENTION_MATRIX.md, and evidence/ADP-S2-P03-T029/{raw_evidence_sample.json, restore_report.json}. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S2-P03-T029/test-results/restore_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): 2016-01 (1 document / 1 version), 2020-07 (1 document / 1 version), and the dense current month 2026-07 (326 month documents / 327 versions / 327 documents with cross-month closure) all restore; the restored counts match the snapshot ground truth; there are zero orphan versions after restore; seven sampled items re-derive the same content_hash (random body) and the same artifact key (random attachment) as the restored versions; and the retention matrix marks the raw official artifact, the published versions, and the canonical identity as PERMANENT / never-delete, with the permanent stores byte-unchanged during the drill and zero permanent deletes. A real finding was fixed mid-task: a single-month isolated restore orphaned one version whose parent document was first seen in an earlier month, so the restore was made referentially closed (pull each version's parent document across partitions), giving zero orphans. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S2-P03-T028 (DuckDB independent open-history verification; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Twenty-eighth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S2-P03), one task per run. Goal: independently verify the open history with DuckDB so the recovery and analysis path is not locked to a single Cloudflare Beta capability. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; an offline verifier reads the T027 open Parquet snapshot with DuckDB -- a different engine from the pyarrow writer -- via read_parquet over local files, with NO R2 SQL and NO R2 Data Catalog and no Cloudflare. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/duckdb_verify.py plus evidence/ADP-S2-P03-T028/{rebuild_report.json, sample_queries.sql}. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S2-P03-T028/test-results/duckdb_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): materializing the full 92-partition snapshot from the committed T027 logical tables and rebuilding with DuckDB yields 498 documents, 500 versions, 46 months (2016-01 to 2026-07), zero orphan version rows, per-month version-creation events that match the logical ground truth exactly, and the derivable signals (repost/multi-source, multi-version, status distribution) -- and every count cross-checks against the committed T027 manifest and logical tables, proving the key documents, versions, events, and signals rebuild from the open format alone with no vendor Beta. The independent rebuild also surfaced a descriptive errata: T027 wrote the month-range end as 2025-10, whereas the true maximum month is 2026-07 (the 46-month count and all data and hashes were always correct); this commit corrects the T027 evidence and spec docs and the T027 CHANGELOG line, while the append-only T027 event is left immutable and this errata records the fix. A dev dependency duckdb==1.1.3 was installed into the user's Python 3.9 user-site as the offline independent engine; the runtime and worker do not use it. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
